installation
--------------

.. start installation

``shippinglabel`` can be installed from pypi or anaconda.

to install with ``pip``:

.. code-block:: bash

	$ python -m pip install shippinglabel

to install with ``conda``:

.. code-block:: bash

	$ conda install -c conda-forge shippinglabel

.. end installation

``shippinglabel`` includes a vendored copy of `trove-classifiers <https://pypi.org/project/trove-classifiers/>`_.
if you install a newer version of ``trove-classifiers`` with pip ``shippinglabel`` will use that version instead.

documentation_summary: The HTML text describes "shippinglabel," a GitHub repository by domdfcoding, which provides utilities for handling packages. It includes features like automated workflows, package hosting, security vulnerability management, and AI-assisted code writing. The repository is public, with options to fork and star. It's licensed under the MIT license and has documentation available on ReadTheDocs. The utilities can be installed via PyPI or Anaconda, and the repository includes a vendored copy of trove-classifiers, with the option to use a newer version if installed separately. The project has 1 star, 3 watchers, 1 fork, and 44 releases, with the latest being version 1.7.1 as of January 11, 2024.
